  "prompt": "Can I put a sleep number matress on a platform frame?",
  "response": "Yes, you can put a Sleep Number mattress on a platform frame, provided the platform frame is sturdy, completely flat, and can support the weight of the mattress and the individuals sleeping on it. Sleep Number mattresses are designed to work with a variety of bed frames, including platform frames. \n\nMake sure the platform frame has sufficient slats or a solid surface to provide uniform support to prevent sagging and ensure the longevity of the mattress. Additionally, if your platform frame has slats, they should be close together (ideally, no more than 2-3 inches apart) to adequately support the air chambers within the mattress.\n\nAlways check the specific recommendations from Sleep Number and the manufacturer of your platform frame to ensure compatibility and to maintain any warranties.",
